3GPP TS 29.122 V18.6.0 T8 reference point for Northbound APIs

AS Session with Required QoS Subscriptions

Read all or queried active subscriptions for the SCS/AS.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
scsAsId
required
string

Identifier of the SCS/AS

query Parameters
Array of objects or objects or objects (IpAddr) non-empty

The IP address(es) of the requested UE(s).

ip-domain
string

The IPv4 address domain identifier. The attribute may only be provided if IPv4 address is included in the ip-addrs query parameter.

mac-addrs
Array of strings (MacAddr48) non-empty [ items^([0-9a-fA-F]{2})((-[0-9a-fA-F]{2}){5})$ ]

The MAC address(es) of the requested UE(s).

Responses

/{apiRoot}/3gpp-as-session-with-qos/v1/{scsAsId}/subscriptions

Creates a new subscription resource.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
scsAsId
required
string

Identifier of the SCS/AS

Request Body schema: application/json
required

Request to create a new subscription resource

self
string (Link)

string formatted according to IETF RFC 3986 identifying a referenced resource.

supportedFeatures
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

dnn
string (Dnn)

String representing a Data Network as defined in clause 9A of 3GPP TS 23.003; it shall contain either a DNN Network Identifier, or a full DNN with both the Network Identifier and Operator Identifier, as specified in 3GPP TS 23.003 clause 9.1.1 and 9.1.2. It shall be coded as string in which the labels are separated by dots (e.g. "Label1.Label2.Label3").

object (Snssai)

When Snssai needs to be converted to string (e.g. when used in maps as key), the string shall be composed of one to three digits "sst" optionally followed by "-" and 6 hexadecimal digits "sd".

notificationDestination
required
string (Link)

string formatted according to IETF RFC 3986 identifying a referenced resource.

exterAppId
string

Identifies the external Application Identifier.

extGroupId
string (ExternalGroupId)

string containing a local identifier followed by "@" and a domain identifier. Both the local identifier and the domain identifier shall be encoded as strings that do not contain any "@" characters. See Clauses 4.6.2 and 4.6.3 of 3GPP TS 23.682 for more information.

gpsi
string (Gpsi) ^(msisdn-[0-9]{5,15}|extid-[^@]+@[^@]+|.+)$

String identifying a Gpsi shall contain either an External Id or an MSISDN. It shall be formatted as follows -External Identifier= "extid-'extid', where 'extid' shall be formatted according to clause 19.7.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an External Identifier.

Array of objects (FlowInfo) non-empty

Describe the data flow which requires QoS.

Array of objects (EthFlowDescription) non-empty

Identifies Ethernet packet flows.

Array of objects (EthFlowInfo) non-empty

Identifies the Ethernet flows which require QoS. Each Ethernet flow consists of a flow idenifer and the corresponding UL and/or DL flows.

Array of objects (UeAddInfo) non-empty

Identifies the list of UE address.

multiModalId
string (MultiModalId)

This data type contains a multi-modal service identifier.

object (ProtocolDescription)

ProtocolDescription contains information to derive PDU set information.

object (ProtocolDescription)

ProtocolDescription contains information to derive PDU set information.

qosReference
string

Identifies a pre-defined QoS information

altQoSReferences
Array of strings non-empty

Identifies an ordered list of pre-defined QoS information. The lower the index of the array for a given entry, the higher the priority.

Array of objects (AlternativeServiceRequirementsData) non-empty

Identifies an ordered list of alternative service requirements that include individual QoS parameter sets. The lower the index of the array for a given entry, the higher the priority.

disUeNotif
boolean

Indicates whether the QoS flow parameters signalling to the UE when the SMF is notified by the NG-RAN of changes in the fulfilled QoS situation is disabled (true) or not (false). Default value is false. The fulfilled situation is either the QoS profile or an Alternative QoS Profile.

ueIpv4Addr
string (schemas-Ipv4Addr)

string identifying a Ipv4 address formatted in the "dotted decimal" notation as defined in IETF RFC 1166.

ipDomain
string
ueIpv6Addr
string (schemas-Ipv6Addr)

string identifying a Ipv6 address formatted according to clause 4 in IETF RFC 5952. The mixed Ipv4 Ipv6 notation according to clause 5 of IETF RFC 5952 shall not be used.

macAddr
string (MacAddr48) ^([0-9a-fA-F]{2})((-[0-9a-fA-F]{2}){5})$

String identifying a MAC address formatted in the hexadecimal notation according to clause 1.1 and clause 2.1 of RFC 7042.

indicating a time in seconds.

boolean

object (TemporalInValidity)

Represents the temporal invalidity conditions, i.e., the time interval(s) during which the AF request is not to be applied.

object (WebsockNotifConfig)

Represents the configuration information for the delivery of notifications over Websockets.

object non-empty

object or object (PduSetQosPara)

Represents the PDU Set level QoS parameters.

boolean

Parameters to update/replace the existing subscription

self
string (Link)

string formatted according to IETF RFC 3986 identifying a referenced resource.

supportedFeatures
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

dnn
string (Dnn)

String representing a Data Network as defined in clause 9A of 3GPP TS 23.003; it shall contain either a DNN Network Identifier, or a full DNN with both the Network Identifier and Operator Identifier, as specified in 3GPP TS 23.003 clause 9.1.1 and 9.1.2. It shall be coded as string in which the labels are separated by dots (e.g. "Label1.Label2.Label3").

object (Snssai)

When Snssai needs to be converted to string (e.g. when used in maps as key), the string shall be composed of one to three digits "sst" optionally followed by "-" and 6 hexadecimal digits "sd".

notificationDestination
required
string (Link)

string formatted according to IETF RFC 3986 identifying a referenced resource.

exterAppId
string

Identifies the external Application Identifier.

extGroupId
string (ExternalGroupId)

string containing a local identifier followed by "@" and a domain identifier. Both the local identifier and the domain identifier shall be encoded as strings that do not contain any "@" characters. See Clauses 4.6.2 and 4.6.3 of 3GPP TS 23.682 for more information.

gpsi
string (Gpsi) ^(msisdn-[0-9]{5,15}|extid-[^@]+@[^@]+|.+)$

String identifying a Gpsi shall contain either an External Id or an MSISDN. It shall be formatted as follows -External Identifier= "extid-'extid', where 'extid' shall be formatted according to clause 19.7.2 of 3GPP TS 23.003 that describes an External Identifier.

Identifier of the SCS/AS

Request Body schema: application/merge-patch+json
required
exterAppId
string

Identifies the external Application Identifier.

Array of objects (FlowInfo) non-empty

Describe the IP data flow which requires QoS.

Array of objects (EthFlowDescription) non-empty

Identifies Ethernet packet flows.

Array of objects (EthFlowInfo) non-empty

Identifies the Ethernet flows which require QoS. Each Ethernet flow consists of a flow idenifer and the corresponding UL and/or DL flows.

Array of objects (UeAddInfo) non-empty

Identifies the list of UE address.

qosReference
string

Pre-defined QoS reference

altQoSReferences
Array of strings non-empty

Identifies an ordered list of pre-defined QoS information. The lower the index of the array for a given entry, the higher the priority.

Array of objects (AlternativeServiceRequirementsData) non-empty

Identifies an ordered list of alternative service requirements that include individual QoS parameter sets. The lower the index of the array for a given entry, the higher the priority.

disUeNotif
boolean

Indicates whether the QoS flow parameters signalling to the UE when the SMF is notified by the NG-RAN of changes in the fulfilled QoS situation is disabled (true) or not (false). The fulfilled situation is either the QoS profile or an Alternative QoS Profile.

object or null (UsageThresholdRm)

Represents the same as the UsageThreshold data type but with the nullable:true property.

object or null (QosMonitoringInformationRm)

Represents the same as the QosMonitoringInformation data type but with the nullable:true property.

object or null (QosMonitoringInformationRm)

Represents the same as the QosMonitoringInformation data type but with the nullable:true property.

directNotifInd
boolean

Indicates whether the direct event notification is requested (true) or not (false) for the provided QoS monitoring parameter(s).

notificationDestination
string (Link)

string formatted according to IETF RFC 3986 identifying a referenced resource.

object (TscQosRequirementRm)

Represents the same as the TscQosRequirement data type but with the nullable:true property.

string or string (UplinkDownlinkSupport)

Represents whether an indication or capability is supported for the UL, the DL or both, UL and DL.

object (TemporalInValidity)

Represents the temporal invalidity conditions, i.e., the time interval(s) during which the AF request is not to be applied.

Array of strings or strings (UserPlaneEvent) non-empty

Represents the updated list of user plane event(s) to which the SCS/AS requests to subscribe to.

object non-empty

Contains media component data for a single-modal data flow(s). The key of the map is the medCompN attribute.

object or null (PduSetQosParaRm)

PduSetQosPara contains removable attributes

object or null (PduSetQosParaRm)

PduSetQosPara contains removable attributes

rTLatencyInd
boolean or null

Indicates the service data flow needs to meet the Round-Trip (RT) latency requirement of the service, when it is included and set to "true".

pdb
integer or null (PacketDelBudgetRm) >= 1

This data type is defined in the same way as the 'PacketDelBudget' data type, but with the OpenAPI 'nullable: true' property.

object or null (ProtocolDescriptionRm)

Describes the modifications to the ProtocolDescription data type.

object or null (ProtocolDescriptionRm)

Describes the modifications to the ProtocolDescription data type.

integer (DurationMilliSecRm)
